      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "The 'Barbie' Review",
      "note": "with Joanna Robinson",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Barbie",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Gerwig and Noah Baumbach's take on the doll and the corporation that makes her, praised as a rare studio movie that's a musical, a comedy, and a feminist argument at once. The group singles out Margot Robbie's performance, the production and costume design (Sarah Greenwood, Jacqueline Durran), America Ferrera's speech, and the Ken material as high points; the Mattel-headquarters plot mechanics as the sag."
        },
        {
          "title": "Oppenheimer",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Released the same weekend as 'Barbie'; the double feature ('Barbenheimer') anchors the opening discussion of the biggest theatrical event since 2019."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "interview",
      "heading": "In conversation",
      "guest": "Greta Gerwig on",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Barbie",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Gerwig on directing Margot Robbie into the part, the year of prep with production designer Sarah Greenwood and costume designer Jacqueline Durran, building Barbie Land with 1959-era techniques, and the Mark Ronson/Andrew Wyatt score woven from Dua Lipa and Billie Eilish songs."
        }
      ]
    }
